The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Lorry runs over man
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      Lorry runs over man
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	A pedestrian in his mid-60s was mowed down by a lorry near the intersection of RG Kar Road and Canal East Road on Sunday morning.        
	Amarnath Saha, a retired railway employee, was crossing the road around 10.20am, when the mishap occurred.        
	Witnesses said the vehicle, which was plying along RG Kar Road, hit Canal East Road without slowing down, catching the pedestrian by surprise. The driver crushed the Beleghata resident under the wheels and sped away.         
	Other pedestrians chased the vehicle but could not make the driver stop, said a police officer.         
	Two groups of residents later put up roadblocks in the area alleging poor traffic surveillance.         
	Help held: Shanti Hore, a 35-year-old help, was arrested on Sunday for allegedly stealing jewellery worth Rs 19 lakh and Rs 50,000 in cash from a traders house on Wood Street on Wednesday.         
	Road mishap: A 55-year-old cyclist, Mihir Bose, sustained injuries after being hit by a bus on route 217A on Rajarhat Road on Sunday afternoon. He was admitted to a local nursing home.        
	The bus was racing another private bus to pick up passengers, said witnesses.        
	Motorcycle stolen: A motorcycle was stolen from Ballygunge Gardens on Saturday evening. Owner Surojit Sikdar of Jadavpur has lodged a complaint.                                                                                                                                                          
